Text: Mmf! This smell...!

Bingo. Found it—a set of fresh footprints in such a
remote area.

Hey, kitty cat! I found it first! It takes less than
a second to sniff out humans in a place like this!
Well, there's always room for error.
Besides, I don't obsess over who found what first.
...You're making fun of me again!

I'm not making fun of you, doggie. I'm just
not interested.
Then quit commenting on everything!

...You know what? I think I know why you butt into
everything I do.
Ha-haaa! You're scared of me, aren't you, kitty cat!

Huh—?! How'd you reach that conclusion,
stupid doggie?!

Well, if you really didn't care, you'd leave me
alone.

And yet you keep on provoking me. Which means...
you're scared of me!

Says the dog whose bark is worse than her bite! Why
the hell would I be scared of you?!
Hm-hmmm!
...I seriously can't with you!
There you go—running away again. What a scaredy-cat!

I'm neither running away nor scared of you! I just
don't want to be a part of this conversation.
I wonder if I picked the wrong pair...

I thought once we got to the site, they would put
aside their differences and work off each other's
strengths, but...
*sigh* I have only myself to blame.

I guess I overestimated how much I knew about Zeta,
or Delta for that matter.

What's the matter, Lady Alpha? It's not gonna rain
today.

The sun doesn't seem that harsh either—did you drink
enough fluids during our break earlier?
Don't worry...it's nothing. Let's follow the trail.
Ngh... I'm starving. I wanna go hunting, Lady Alpha.
No hunting for food today.

We've brought enough supplies, and overeating will
dull your hunting skills.
Actually...you've got a point!

I can't muster up much strength when I'm starving...
but a little bit of hunger can actually motivate me!

Never thought of it like that, even though it always
happens... You're a genius, Lady Alpha!
Heh... Thanks.

Zeta should return soon with intel on the area
surrounding their hideout. It's important that
we know not only what we're hunting, but
where we're hunting.
...That's something the kitty cat is good at.
And something you're not.

I wish you could learn...to respect others who can do
the important things you can't do yourself.

I can't play spy, write things, open a store, play
musical instruments, or invent...but it doesn't
bother me.

I can hunt better than anyone, and that's all that
matters!
Well, sure...

There currently aren't many advantages for everyone
in the Seven Shadow to possess the same skill sets.

That's why I don't think I need that sword training
you mentioned!
You're definitely doing that.
Ugh...
Well, I'll do it if you let me eat something!
Really?
...Maybe!
*sigh* Here.
Whoa! Wait, this is tiny.

It's a Tuna Tempura Burger from Tuna King. This
one's a prototype we haven't released yet.
I'll give it a try! *munch*

Goodness, Delta, how can you taste it if you gobble
it down in one bite?!
This would definitely go better with rice than bread.
That would make it more of a rice ball than a burger.
Why don't you make it a rice sandwich?

How are we supposed to sandwich anything between
rice—?

Wait, hold on... We could harden the rice by
flattening it and grilling the sides.

A Tuna Tempura Rice Burger—it might be worth pitching
to Gamma.

Thank you for the unexpected inspiration, Delta.
I would never have come up with that idea on
my own.
Really?

Yes, it's down to your uniqueness of not being bound
by common sense.

You know what? Maybe there's more to all seven of us
having different abilities.

Not really sure what you're on about, but if my
uniqueness means I don't have to sword train—
You're definitely still doing that.
Awooo...
Heheh.
